## Code Examples

### NEVER This
```typescript
// ❌ NEVER use any
function parseHop(data: any): any {
  return {
    name: data.NAME,
    alpha: data.ALPHA
  };
}
```

### ALWAYS This
```typescript
// ✅ Proper typing
function parseHop(data: unknown): Hop {
  const validated = HopSchema.parse(data);
  return {
    name: validated.NAME,
    alphaAcid: validated.ALPHA,
    amount: validated.AMOUNT,
    // ... full mapping
  };
}
```

## AI Assistant Instructions

When generating code for this library:
1. NEVER use `any` type - I will reject any code with `any`
2. Always validate input data before processing
3. Maintain separation between internal types (camelCase) and BeerXML schema (UPPERCASE)
4. Include comprehensive error messages with context
5. Write pure functions where possible
6. Include JSDoc comments for all public APIs
7. Consider both import and export scenarios
8. Test edge cases and malformed input
9. Keep the library zero-dependency
10. Preserve unknown fields for forward compatibility
